caller_intent: Gary called to inform Betty Hill about a discrepancy in a VIN number (O5 vs. O6) related to a previous insurance change request.
resolution_steps: Betty acknowledges the call and explains the VIN was correctly processed as an O5 (2005 model) despite initial confusion about the year model.
Clarifies that the VIN itself was accurate, but the year model (O6) was incorrect in the system.
Ensures Gary understands the documents he receives will reflect the correct VIN and year model.
knowledge_required: Understanding of VIN number formats and their relation to vehicle year models
systems_referenced: Alliance Insurance Services internal policy management system
summary: Betty Hill resolved a confusion with Gary about a VIN number discrepancy, clarifying that the VIN was correct (O5/2005) but the year model was initially misprocessed. The issue was resolved through direct communication, ensuring Gary would not be confused by documents related to the policy change.
